{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Cache keys generated from identical query parameters are always identical, and keys from different parameters never collide.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is deterministic key-derivation logic at a single function/object boundary (normalization + hashing/serialization). Real failures here are algorithmic (ordering, type coercion, canonicalization), not dependent on DB, OS, or external services.","test_description":"Unit-test the key builder directly with table-driven and property-based cases: same semantic params in different input orders produce identical keys; different params produce different keys across a large randomized corpus; include edge cases (nulls, arrays, nested maps, numeric/string distinctions).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.92,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The TTL for a cache entry is computed correctly based on the data category's configured freshness rule (e.g., user profiles = 5 minutes, product catalog = 1 hour).","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"TTL selection is rule/config mapping logic. The failure boundary is local computation (category->duration), not module handoff requiring real infra.","test_description":"Unit-test TTL calculator with injected config fixture: assert exact durations per category, default/fallback behavior, boundary values, and invalid/missing category handling.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When memory usage exceeds the configured threshold, the eviction strategy switches from LRU to LFU as specified in the configuration.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The bug typically appears at module boundaries: memory-pressure signal/metrics provider + config + strategy selector + cache policy wiring. A pure unit of selector logic can miss real failures in handoff units/threshold units/wiring.","test_description":"Integration test wiring real cache manager modules with an in-process memory-pressure provider stub and real config loader. Drive memory usage across threshold and assert active policy changes from LRU to LFU at runtime, including hysteresis/edge threshold behavior if defined.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A write to the underlying PostgreSQL table invalidates all cache entries whose keys match the affected rows.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure occurs when DB write events, invalidation mapper, and cache index interact. Mocking this boundary can hide trigger/mapping bugs. Per level defs, local DB-backed module interaction is Integration (not necessarily System).","test_description":"Integration test with real cache modules plus a local PostgreSQL instance/test DB: seed rows and cache entries, execute UPDATE/INSERT/DELETE on target table, run invalidation hook/listener path, then assert matching keys are removed while non-matching keys remain.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.17,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The eviction policy removes the correct entries — least-recently-used under LRU, least-frequently-used under LFU — when the cache is full.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Correct victim selection depends on interaction between cache storage, access-tracking metadata, and active policy mode. Unit-testing the policy function alone can miss metadata update/order bugs in real cache operations.","test_description":"Integration test using real in-memory cache implementation: fill to capacity, perform controlled access patterns to set recency/frequency, trigger overflow under LRU then LFU mode, and assert exact evicted keys in each mode.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.63,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
